    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) is a masterclass in lightweight engineering, preserved in collector-grade condition. It features the original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, delivering seamless boost transition and high-RPM stability. The longitudinal front-midship engine placement ensures a perfect 50/50 weight distribution, paired with a factory-spec four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for surgical turn-in precision. The vacuum system and cooling architecture have been meticulously maintained to prevent heat soak, ensuring the thermal integrity of the apex seals. With zero modifications to the intake or exhaust manifolds, this FD remains a mechanically transparent example of JDM performance history, free of typical chassis flex or interior degradation.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
